OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1772025561
OL,3,CPublic sector pay deals dominant
OL,4,Creason for Stormont 'overspend'
OL,6,FNorthern Ireland's budget watchdog has
OL,7,Fwarned continued public sector pay
OL,8,Fdeals are the dominant reason for
OL,9,F'over spending' at Stormont.
OL,11,FThe Northern Ireland Fiscal Council
OL,12,Fhas said a #400million package to help
OL,13,Fbalance the books is a de-facto bail
OL,14,Fout from the Treasury which masks a
OL,15,Fdeeper fiscal pressure.
OL,17,FThe Council has published its
OL,18,Fassessment of Finance Minister John
OL,19,FO'Dowd's multi-year budget calling on
OL,20,Fthe Executive to "address the
OL,21,Funderlying causes of overspending".
OL,26,@|D@ROU}D@bO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/9
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1772025561
OL,3,CPublic sector pay deals dominant
OL,4,Creason for Stormont 'overspend'
OL,6,FSir Robert Chote, Chairman of the
OL,7,FFiscal Council said: "If you have a
OL,8,Fcombination of the desire to meet pay
OL,9,Fparity and you have still a public
OL,10,Fsector that is relatively large in
OL,11,FNorthern Ireland - with a lot more
OL,12,Fpublic sector workers per head of
OL,13,Fpopulation here than elsewhere - then
OL,14,Fthe way in which the funding formula
OL,15,Fworks in bringing money over from
OL,16,FLondon, that is just setting yourself
OL,17,Fup for for a problem.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/9
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1772025561
OL,3,CPublic sector pay deals dominant
OL,4,Creason for Stormont 'overspend'
OL,6,F"If the Executive wants to prioritise
OL,7,Fpay parity, which they have done in
OL,8,Fboth Health and Education, the
OL,9,FNorthern Ireland Civil Service said
OL,10,Fthat is not affordable with the
OL,11,Famounts of money available.
OL,13,F"But the Executive agreed that
OL,14,FMinisters should direct the Civil
OL,15,FService to go ahead with that.
OL,17,F"Then you are heading for the
OL,18,Flikelihood of more overspends in the
OL,19,Ffuture."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/9
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1772025561
OL,3,CPublic sector pay deals dominant
OL,4,Creason for Stormont 'overspend'
OL,6,FThe Executive is engaging with the
OL,7,FTreasury on a process to assess
OL,8,Ffunding in Northern Ireland - the hope
OL,9,Fis to show not enough money is
OL,10,Fallocated to cover costs.
OL,12,FFinance Minister John O'Dowd expects
OL,13,Fthat process to get underway
OL,14,Fimminently.
OL,16,F"I want that completed so we can sit
OL,17,Fdown at a political level and have
OL,18,Fserious discussions about how the
OL,19,FExecutive is funded to deliver public
OL,20,Fservices.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/9
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1772025561
OL,3,CPublic sector pay deals dominant
OL,4,Creason for Stormont 'overspend'
OL,6,F"It is clear, in my opinion, that we
OL,7,Fhave been underfunded for many, many
OL,8,Fyears.
OL,10,F"I think there is a shared view of
OL,11,Fthat around the Executive table," he
OL,12,Fsaid.
OL,14,FWhile some think that process is a
OL,15,Fpositive, there are those who do not
OL,16,Fagree.
OL,18,FLeader of the Opposition Matthew
OL,19,FO'Toole said: "It feels a little bit
OL,20,Flike the proverbial bald men arguing
OL,21,Fover the comb.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/9
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1772025561
OL,3,CPublic sector pay deals dominant
OL,4,Creason for Stormont 'overspend'
OL,6,F"I was in Hillsborough Castle a couple
OL,7,Fof years ago when there was a Treasury
OL,8,Fofficial there on finger wagging duty
OL,9,Ftelling us all how we were supposed to
OL,10,Fget on with transformation.
OL,12,F"That transformation has not happened,
OL,13,Fso now we are undermining devolution
OL,14,Fby inviting the Treasury back in to
OL,15,Ftell us again how it is not working."
OL,17,FStormont departments are on course to
OL,18,Foverspend their budgets by almost
OL,19,F#460million.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/9
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1772025561
OL,3,CPublic sector pay deals dominant
OL,4,Creason for Stormont 'overspend'
OL,6,FThe Treasury has stepped in to allow
OL,7,F#400million to be put on the
OL,8,FGovernment credit card and paid off
OL,9,Fover the next three years.
OL,11,FThat bailout creates a credibility
OL,12,Fchallenge the Fiscal Council warns.
OL,14,F"They have agreed to pay it back in
OL,15,Fchunks over the next three years,
OL,16,Fwhich obviously makes life a bit
OL,17,Feasier for the Executive.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/9
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1772025561
OL,3,CPublic sector pay deals dominant
OL,4,Creason for Stormont 'overspend'
OL,6,F"It means that the next year in
OL,7,Fparticular is not quite as challenging
OL,8,Fas otherwise would be, although still
OL,9,Fvery challenging.
OL,11,F"But you are, as you say, kicking the
OL,12,Fthe can down the road, and if
OL,13,FMinisters expect there to be more
OL,14,Fsupport of that sort in the future,
OL,15,Fthen you are reducing the incentive
OL,16,Ffor them to get to grips with the
OL,17,Funderlying factors that are leading to
OL,18,Fthe pressure to overspend," Sir Robert
OL,19,FChote said.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/9
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
